# Digital Gas Stove with Gas Leakage Detection

# Project Overview

The **Digital Child Lock Gas Stove** is an embedded system designed to improve kitchen safety by preventing unauthorized stove operation and detecting gas leakage. The system uses a password-based child lock mechanism and a gas sensor to monitor LPG leaks continuously. When gas leakage is detected, the system activates an alarm and automatically controls the gas flow using a solenoid valve, minimizing the risk of accidents.

This project demonstrates the practical application of embedded systems in enhancing household safety and was developed as part of an academic project.


# Objectives

* Control gas flow using a solenoid valve.
* Implement a password-based child lock mechanism.
* Detect LPG gas leakage in real time.
* Trigger an alarm when gas leakage is detected.
* Improve kitchen safety and prevent accidental gas-related hazards.


